HEADWORD: Tmesis
<hw>Tme"sis</hw> <pr>(m⟦emac⟧"s⟦icr⟧s <it>or</it> t'm⟦emac⟧"s⟦icr⟧s;
277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., from Gr. <grk>tmh^sis</grk> a
cutting, fr. <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut.]</ety> <fld>(Gram.)</fld>
<def>The separation of the parts of a compound word by the intervention
of one or more words; <as>as, <ex>in what place soever</ex>, for
<ex>whatsoever place</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

